Assigned to: Appropriations
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public School Construction and Renovation – Solar Canopies for School
3 Parking Lots – Underground Infrastructure
4 FOR the purpose of requiring that certain construction projects or major renovation
5 projects of public school buildings be designed, engineered, and constructed in a
6 manner so that school parking lots are equipped with the appropriate underground
7 infrastructure necessary to support solar canopy installation; and generally relating
8 to public school construction and renovations.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Education
11 Section 5–331
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Education
17 5–331.
18 FOR EACH CONSTRUCTION PROJECT OR MAJOR RENOVATION PROJECT OF A
19 PUBLIC SCHOOL BUILDING PROPOSED AFTER DECEMBER 31, 2025, THAT INCLUDES
20 THE CONSTRUCTION OR RENOVATION OF A SCHOOL PARKING LOT, THE STATE
21 SHALL REQUIRE THAT THE PROJECT BE DESIGNED, ENGINEERED, AND
22 CONSTRUCTED IN A MANNER SO THAT THE PARKING LOT IS EQUIPPED WITH THE
23 APPROPRIATE UNDERGROUND INFRASTRUCTURE NECESSARY TO SUPPORT SOLAR
24 CANOPY INSTALLATION.
